1
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:37,954
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

2
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:44,544
You can call her big sis.

3
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:46,171
Everyone knows she's old.

4
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:54,345
Well, <i>we</i> know.

5
00:01:03,605 --> 00:01:04,689
I'm sorry.

6
00:01:09,944 --> 00:01:11,112
Mommy!

7
00:01:12,405 --> 00:01:13,239
Bom?

8
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:16,534
Bom.

9
00:01:17,994 --> 00:01:18,828
Bom!

10
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:26,336
Bom, I'm so sorry.

11
00:01:41,309 --> 00:01:42,352
What?

12
00:01:43,102 --> 00:01:43,978
Hong Jang-mi?

13
00:01:44,062 --> 00:01:46,523
The slush fund hidden under her name

14
00:01:47,482 --> 00:01:48,525
has all been withdrawn.

15
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:53,029
Are you saying
she went in person to withdraw it?

16
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:53,947
<i>Yes.</i>

17
00:01:54,030 --> 00:01:57,700
The branch manager said
she had an authorization letter

18
00:01:58,284 --> 00:01:59,702
<i>and that he even spoke to you.</i>

19
00:02:02,163 --> 00:02:03,039
Also,

20
00:02:03,581 --> 00:02:07,377
all three financial institutions
in Chungseo were looted.

21
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:14,259
Bring the branch manager of Saenara Bank
to Seoul right now.

22
00:02:16,261 --> 00:02:17,137
All right.

23
00:02:31,693 --> 00:02:33,236
EMPLOYEE PERSONNEL RECORD

24
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:34,404
Hong Jang-mi.

25
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:36,364
You've got some nerve.

26
00:02:38,241 --> 00:02:40,285
How dare you touch that 24 billion won?

27
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:05,602
You guys are secretly planning something,
aren't you?

28
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:09,397
What do you mean?

29
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:17,697
Can I come with you to the dorms?

30
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:20,074
I still have some stuff there
that I need to pick up.

31
00:03:20,158 --> 00:03:22,285
I already called the RA
and got her permission.

32
00:03:22,368 --> 00:03:23,494
I figured I could go today…

33
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:25,455
No. You can't.

34
00:03:25,538 --> 00:03:27,457
Tell me what you need,
and I'll send them to you.

35
00:03:29,709 --> 00:03:31,336
There really is something you're hiding.

36
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:35,089
Come on, what is it?
Don't leave me out again.

37
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:39,052
I think we can tell Ms. Kang, no?

38
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:40,887
I mean, Big Al knows too.

39
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:42,096
No.

40
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:43,932
She's way further up the family tree.

41
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:46,226
Albert knows?

42
00:03:46,726 --> 00:03:49,479
Why won't you tell me when even he knows?

43
00:04:23,471 --> 00:04:24,472
Hey, you…

44
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:36,859
Thank you for coming
all this way to Seoul.

45
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:38,403
I needed to confirm something with you.

46
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:42,156
Was it her who withdrew the money?

47
00:04:45,159 --> 00:04:47,287
Yes, it was her.

48
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:48,454
Hong Jang-mi.

49
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:50,498
She came and withdrew it in person.

50
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:53,918
Ms. Song, we spoke
on the phone then, remember?

51
00:04:54,502 --> 00:04:55,878
That wasn't me.

52
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:57,505
Pardon?

53
00:05:07,015 --> 00:05:08,308
This is Hong Jang-mi?

54
00:05:09,517 --> 00:05:11,644
Are you sure it's not Hong Keum-bo?

55
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:28,453
That shell company

56
00:05:29,037 --> 00:05:31,372
buying up the Hanmin bonds
you mentioned last time.

57
00:05:32,081 --> 00:05:35,001
I confirmed
it was being funded by DK Ventures.

58
00:05:36,336 --> 00:05:37,337
We expected as much.

59
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:41,174
It's not too late
to let them handle it on their own.

60
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:44,886
I'm sure if Chairman Kang knew
what DK Ventures was scheming,

61
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:46,637
he'd figure something out.

62
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:48,264
Are you telling me to back out?

63
00:05:48,347 --> 00:05:49,682
No.

64
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:54,103
I'm just saying we should give
Chairman Kang Pil-beom a chance

65
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:55,688
to save Hanmin through his own efforts.

66
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:59,192
The privileged get
all the second chances in this world,

67
00:05:59,942 --> 00:06:02,111
while the rest get only one shot.

68
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:04,405
I'm just worried
about the dangers you'll face.

69
00:06:04,989 --> 00:06:06,908
I believe this will be my last chance.

70
00:06:08,117 --> 00:06:09,911
I'm going to start by knocking down

71
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:11,954
Chairman Kang's pawns one by one.

72
00:06:24,383 --> 00:06:26,427
EPISODE 13: WITCH HUNT

73
00:06:27,678 --> 00:06:28,888
Hong Jang-mi.

74
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:32,433
When are you going to grow up?

75
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:33,726
ULLALA CHICKEN

76
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:35,770
Hey, we have a customer. Welcome!

77
00:06:35,853 --> 00:06:37,271
We have a customer. Welcome, sir.

78
00:06:37,355 --> 00:06:38,773
Have a seat wherever you'd like.

79
00:06:41,109 --> 00:06:42,568
What would you like to order?

80
00:06:43,861 --> 00:06:47,073
Can I get a fried chicken and a soda?

81
00:06:47,156 --> 00:06:48,741
- Yes, sure. It'll be right up.
- Thanks.

82
00:06:49,867 --> 00:06:54,122
Your sister spent all that money on you
for that boarding cram school.

83
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:56,666
The least you can do is study
as if your life depended on it,

84
00:06:56,749 --> 00:06:57,792
not run away!

85
00:06:57,875 --> 00:07:00,211
I just don't have the brains for it.

86
00:07:00,294 --> 00:07:01,879
I'm not cut out for school.

87
00:07:02,463 --> 00:07:05,091
And you just don't know
what that place is like.

88
00:07:05,174 --> 00:07:07,009
Even Keum-bo
wouldn't be able to last there.

89
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:11,347
How can sisters be such polar opposites?

90
00:07:11,430 --> 00:07:13,057
I, Hong Jang-mi,

91
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:15,768
can never be like Hong Keum-bo.

92
00:07:15,852 --> 00:07:17,478
Just give up already, Mom.

93
00:07:17,562 --> 00:07:18,855
Where do you think you're going?

94
00:07:18,938 --> 00:07:20,481
- Get back here!
- Stop it.

95
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:25,153
I'm sorry about all that.

96
00:07:26,195 --> 00:07:27,280
She must be your youngest daughter.

97
00:07:27,363 --> 00:07:29,866
Yes, we have two princesses.

98
00:07:30,783 --> 00:07:32,952
That's our youngest,
and the eldest works in Yeouido.

99
00:07:33,035 --> 00:07:34,245
Yeouido?

100
00:07:35,371 --> 00:07:36,873
You must be so proud of her.

101
00:07:38,916 --> 00:07:40,084
Yes, I am.

102
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:41,711
- Just give me a moment.
- Sure.

103
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:44,547
Go.

104
00:07:57,226 --> 00:08:01,105
We need to reallocate the slush fund.

105
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:06,027
Do you mean fund rebalancing?

106
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:08,070
No, not that.

107
00:08:09,238 --> 00:08:11,324
In the case that things go awry,

108
00:08:11,824 --> 00:08:14,827
we should make preparations
to move it offshore.

109
00:08:14,911 --> 00:08:15,786
I spoke to

110
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:18,372
the head of the Board of Audit
and Inspection yesterday.

111
00:08:18,956 --> 00:08:20,708
They're launching a special audit

112
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:25,713
into the foreign exchange crisis
before the new administration takes over.

113
00:08:25,796 --> 00:08:29,842
They're clearly looking to assign blame.

114
00:08:30,676 --> 00:08:33,888
That could put us in the crossfire,

115
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:36,182
so let's make sure

116
00:08:36,265 --> 00:08:39,560
our domestic funds are in order
by the end of January.

117
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:43,272
Yes, sir.

118
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:44,690
Good.

119
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:11,217
PERSONAL INFORMATION FORM

120
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:23,980
PERSONAL INFORMATION FORM
HONG KEUM-BO

121
00:09:24,063 --> 00:09:25,940
EMPLOYEE PERSONNEL RECORD

122
00:09:26,023 --> 00:09:27,108
HONG CHUN-SEOP, FATHER
KIM SOON-JUNG, MOTHER

123
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:30,486
HONG JANG-MI, YOUNGER SISTER

124
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:38,786
If the chairman finds out
the OW's slush fund is gone,

125
00:09:40,496 --> 00:09:42,707
thirty years of work
will go down the drain.

126
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:53,384
Hey.

127
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:54,468
Ju-ran.

128
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,346
Yeah, I looked into it.

129
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:03,102
I went to the restaurant
that Hong Keum-bo's parents run,

130
00:10:03,185 --> 00:10:05,313
and I even saw
the real Hong Jang-mi there.

131
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:10,026
It turns out Hong Keum-bo has been
impersonating her this whole time.

132
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,279
So?

133
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:16,991
Should I deal with her like I did
Kim I-gyeong from the Songwi Branch?

134
00:10:18,701 --> 00:10:19,535
No.

135
00:10:20,745 --> 00:10:21,996
If we act rashly,

136
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:24,957
we may lose both the money
and the chairman's trust.

137
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:27,126
And she couldn't have done this alone.

138
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:29,170
The branch manager told us

139
00:10:29,962 --> 00:10:31,589
that she had an accomplice

140
00:10:31,672 --> 00:10:33,633
who answered the phone
and impersonated me.

141
00:10:38,387 --> 00:10:39,805
SEOUL CITY DORMITORY
FOR SINGLE FEMALE WORKERS

142
00:10:41,515 --> 00:10:43,726
I hear you're roommates.

143
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:46,812
Yes, that's right.

144
00:10:47,438 --> 00:10:49,231
I'll be in touch, so stand by.

145
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:03,913
Ms. Go.

146
00:11:03,996 --> 00:11:06,040
You live in the same dorm
as Hong Jang-mi, right?

147
00:11:06,999 --> 00:11:08,292
Yes, that's right.

148
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:09,585
Do you remember…

149
00:11:10,961 --> 00:11:13,881
when Madam Choi visited
the director's office and made a scene?

150
00:11:15,675 --> 00:11:17,426
That happens quite frequently, so…

151
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:21,555
Yes, I remember.

152
00:11:24,016 --> 00:11:25,017
Can you tell me…

153
00:11:26,727 --> 00:11:28,938
your whereabouts at that time?

154
00:11:29,814 --> 00:11:31,190
The other assistants told me

155
00:11:31,732 --> 00:11:34,985
that you weren't at the Admin office.

156
00:11:38,697 --> 00:11:40,032
I was in the president's office.

157
00:11:40,699 --> 00:11:44,537
President Shin was asking me
about Director Kang,

158
00:11:45,121 --> 00:11:49,083
since as you're well aware,
I also shared the dorms with her.

159
00:11:53,170 --> 00:11:55,339
When I scouted you for Hanmin,

160
00:11:56,298 --> 00:11:57,925
there was a minor commotion.

161
00:11:59,218 --> 00:12:00,845
Eulbuk Bank,

162
00:12:01,804 --> 00:12:03,264
Yeosan Farmers' Bank,

163
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:05,015
and Saenara Bank in Yeosu.

164
00:12:06,308 --> 00:12:07,560
The branch managers there

165
00:12:08,436 --> 00:12:11,689
wanted to bring embezzlement
and theft charges against you.

166
00:12:14,483 --> 00:12:15,359
I'm the one

167
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:17,695
who covered that up.

168
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:21,991
One call from me is all it takes

169
00:12:22,074 --> 00:12:23,659
to rile them up again.

170
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:26,745
So,

171
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:30,875
you should be very careful
about the side you take.

172
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:34,044
"Don't bite the hand that feeds you."

173
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:36,172
"If you do,

174
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:37,339
it'll be your undoing."

175
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:39,592
They say that for a reason.

176
00:12:43,846 --> 00:12:45,598
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

177
00:12:45,681 --> 00:12:48,184
I think Ms. Song has caught on.

178
00:12:48,767 --> 00:12:52,396
She summoned me today
and threatened me with my past,

179
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:53,772
telling me to join her side.

180
00:12:53,856 --> 00:12:54,982
You told Ms. Hong, right?

181
00:12:55,065 --> 00:12:56,775
I told her right away.

182
00:12:56,859 --> 00:12:59,653
I told her to be extra careful,
but you know she never listens.

183
00:13:00,779 --> 00:13:04,200
What do you normally do
when you find yourself cornered like this?

184
00:13:05,534 --> 00:13:07,495
I run and don't look back.

185
00:13:20,424 --> 00:13:22,092
Just relax. You're still recovering.

186
00:13:22,176 --> 00:13:24,011
I'm being discharged tomorrow.

187
00:13:29,099 --> 00:13:31,352
The RA caught us with Bom,

188
00:13:31,435 --> 00:13:33,938
so I had my parents in Incheon
look after her.

189
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:38,526
My parents suggested
that you and Bom stay with them.

190
00:13:43,531 --> 00:13:44,740
Thank you.

191
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:49,495
You're thanking Hong Keum-bo
and not Hong Jang-mi, right?

192
00:13:51,163 --> 00:13:53,791
I thought I had everyone fooled,

193
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:55,793
but I had failed from the start.

194
00:13:57,711 --> 00:14:00,798
Thank you for keeping my secret.

195
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:02,841
It was nothing.

196
00:14:03,425 --> 00:14:07,137
I'm the one who left you
with all sorts of requests,

197
00:14:08,097 --> 00:14:10,558
only to survive a suicide attempt
and burden you even more

198
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:12,101
with my daughter and me.

199
00:14:13,978 --> 00:14:16,105
But you know…

200
00:14:19,149 --> 00:14:20,568
I really wanted to live.

201
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:39,795
My parents run a fried chicken restaurant.

202
00:14:40,504 --> 00:14:43,048
If you feel that bad,
help them out when they're busy.

203
00:14:44,383 --> 00:14:48,095
Although they're rarely busy
because of the recession and all.

204
00:14:55,978 --> 00:14:57,521
Where's Room 315?

205
00:14:58,147 --> 00:14:59,773
It's that way.

206
00:15:10,492 --> 00:15:11,368
Ms. Hong.

207
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:13,579
No, that's not right.

208
00:15:13,662 --> 00:15:16,832
Perhaps I should be more respectful
and address you as "Inspector Hong"?

209
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:19,752
Showing up unannounced
is already pretty disrespectful.

210
00:15:21,086 --> 00:15:22,338
Are you here for an overdue visit?

211
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:28,093
I have no business with some forgettable,
nameless bank teller.

212
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:31,513
You should remember her.

213
00:15:32,306 --> 00:15:33,349
You all are responsible.

214
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:44,777
Do you even know whose money you touched?

215
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:48,405
Of course, I do.

216
00:15:48,489 --> 00:15:51,742
It's Hong Jang-mi's money
that fell out of the sky and into her lap.

217
00:15:56,705 --> 00:15:58,958
Ms. Song,
you initiated the physical force.

218
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:03,837
What happened to the champion of justice
leading the crusade against Hanmin?

219
00:16:03,921 --> 00:16:06,924
I see even the esteemed Hong Keum-bo
is tempted by money.

220
00:16:07,549 --> 00:16:09,843
Did you fake your identity to get the job

221
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:12,513
so you could trade in your experience
for 24 billion won?

222
00:16:12,596 --> 00:16:14,223
You were after the money all along!

223
00:16:15,432 --> 00:16:16,558
You should know

224
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:18,018
you won't be alive to spend it.

225
00:16:18,769 --> 00:16:20,145
How sad your parents will be

226
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:23,190
when their beloved daughter
meets her untimely death.

227
00:16:23,273 --> 00:16:26,360
Your own future should concern you
more than mine does.

228
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:28,737
Do you think
Chairman Kang will let you live

229
00:16:28,821 --> 00:16:30,698
once he finds out his 24 billion is gone?

230
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:43,252
The accomplice who impersonated me
to help you withdraw from Saenara Bank was

231
00:16:43,335 --> 00:16:44,169
Go Bok-hee, right?

232
00:16:45,754 --> 00:16:47,131
Are you even aware

233
00:16:47,214 --> 00:16:51,135
of how many banks and securities firms
she has ripped off so far?

234
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:52,928
Do you really think
the money you two stole

235
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:54,304
will be safe in her hands?

236
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:57,808
If you want your 24 billion back,
you will do as I say.

237
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:01,854
I'll hand over the money
if you get rid of President Shin.

238
00:17:03,355 --> 00:17:04,857
President Shin?

239
00:17:04,940 --> 00:17:06,900
He's your real enemy,

240
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:09,611
the one looking to strip Hanmin bare
and swallow it whole.

241
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:12,031
If Hanmin goes down,

242
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:14,324
both your hard work and mine
will go up in smoke.

243
00:17:18,912 --> 00:17:20,205
Be sure to answer my calls.

244
00:17:46,857 --> 00:17:48,233
So what did Ms. Song say?

245
00:17:48,317 --> 00:17:49,318
Did she say she'd do it?

246
00:17:49,401 --> 00:17:50,694
That she'd get rid of President Shin?

247
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:52,488
I didn't bother waiting for a response.

248
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:54,281
She has no other choice but to follow.

249
00:17:55,532 --> 00:17:58,285
After being loyal to Chairman Kang
all this time,

250
00:17:58,368 --> 00:18:00,496
how'd she end up in Hong Keum-bo's snare?

251
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:01,914
Oh, right.

252
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:05,709
She mentioned your name
almost immediately.

253
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:08,295
She also knew
about your past embezzlement.

254
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:13,050
Looks like work tomorrow
is going to be torture.

255
00:18:15,427 --> 00:18:17,596
A-E-I-O-U.

256
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:20,557
Did you call for me, ma'am?

257
00:18:22,935 --> 00:18:25,437
You know, I've been wondering for a while.

258
00:18:25,521 --> 00:18:28,774
How do you manage to maintain
such a calm smile on your face

259
00:18:28,857 --> 00:18:31,443
when the higher-ups
spew nonsense and dig into you?

260
00:18:35,656 --> 00:18:36,532
It's so I don't lose.

261
00:18:37,741 --> 00:18:40,744
You lose if you show tears
or falter in that moment.

262
00:18:42,246 --> 00:18:45,040
I know how I really feel
behind that smile.

263
00:18:49,419 --> 00:18:50,754
Now I know too.

264
00:18:54,007 --> 00:18:56,510
I'm afraid I don't understand, ma'am.

265
00:18:57,678 --> 00:18:58,637
Watch and learn.

266
00:19:03,350 --> 00:19:04,935
Yes, I understand.

267
00:19:09,439 --> 00:19:12,025
I just faxed over
Go Bok-hee's personnel file.

268
00:19:12,109 --> 00:19:13,318
EMPLOYEE PERSONNEL RECORD

269
00:19:13,402 --> 00:19:15,487
Her older brother's name is Go Bok-cheol.

270
00:19:16,071 --> 00:19:19,158
He's a convicted violent offender
who was just released a month ago.

271
00:19:19,783 --> 00:19:20,617
Find him.

272
00:19:32,462 --> 00:19:34,298
Hey, what's with the long face?

273
00:19:35,674 --> 00:19:39,511
I know it's the recession and all,
but you need to keep your spirits up.

274
00:19:42,681 --> 00:19:44,141
How are the preparations
for the engagement going?

275
00:19:46,685 --> 00:19:48,228
I couldn't be busier.

276
00:19:48,312 --> 00:19:50,355
I have another packed day ahead.

277
00:19:50,439 --> 00:19:52,566
I have a catering testing at lunch,

278
00:19:52,649 --> 00:19:53,650
and in the afternoon,

279
00:19:53,734 --> 00:19:55,903
I'm checking Nora and President Shin's
astrological compatibility.

280
00:19:57,738 --> 00:19:58,780
Ma'am.

281
00:20:00,157 --> 00:20:01,116
Have you looked into

282
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,035
President Shin's
past relationships as well?

283
00:20:05,537 --> 00:20:06,914
Why the sudden interest?

284
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:09,791
As you're well aware,

285
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:11,793
he's lived abroad for a long time,

286
00:20:11,877 --> 00:20:14,129
so the available intel was a bit limited.

287
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:16,506
He dated his first love in college,

288
00:20:16,590 --> 00:20:18,717
and they got their first jobs
at the same company.

289
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:19,635
That's about it.

290
00:20:20,844 --> 00:20:21,678
But you know what?

291
00:20:22,304 --> 00:20:23,972
She has such a funny name.

292
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:26,099
"Hong Keum-bo." Isn't it funny?

293
00:20:27,184 --> 00:20:28,560
Did you say Hong Keum-bo?

294
00:20:28,644 --> 00:20:31,855
You know, like the Hong Kong action star
Hung Kam-bo.

295
00:20:35,859 --> 00:20:37,527
Don't tell Nora.

296
00:20:39,571 --> 00:20:41,073
I should go and escort the chairman.

297
00:20:42,699 --> 00:20:43,617
"Hong Keum-bo."

298
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:53,252
So she's targeting Shin Jung-woo
for a reason.

299
00:20:57,130 --> 00:20:59,716
There's a party buying up Hanmin stocks?

300
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:01,969
<i>They acquired over 9% last week alone.</i>

301
00:21:02,052 --> 00:21:04,346
- Is it an investment trust company?
<i>- An investment trust company?</i>

302
00:21:04,429 --> 00:21:06,932
<i>I'm not sure,</i>
<i>but it's definitely not an individual.</i>

303
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:08,850
<i>There haven't been public disclosures yet.</i>

304
00:21:09,518 --> 00:21:11,061
All right, I'll look into it.

305
00:21:20,153 --> 00:21:21,780
Ms. Go, can I see you for a moment?

306
00:21:30,747 --> 00:21:33,458
Do you happen to know
of a long-tenured employee

307
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:37,004
who has their finger
on the pulse of the securities industry?

308
00:21:37,087 --> 00:21:38,880
May I ask what this is regarding?

309
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:41,675
We lost many people
during the restructuring.

310
00:21:41,758 --> 00:21:45,429
I would say Mr. Cha Jung-il from Research
has a strong grasp of market sentiment.

311
00:21:46,346 --> 00:21:47,848
Let him know I'd like a meeting.

312
00:21:47,931 --> 00:21:48,974
Yes, sir.

313
00:22:01,111 --> 00:22:02,654
You asked to see me, sir?

314
00:22:03,238 --> 00:22:04,114
Yes.

315
00:22:04,197 --> 00:22:07,367
I'd like to ask you for a favor

316
00:22:07,451 --> 00:22:08,410
off the record.

317
00:22:08,493 --> 00:22:10,871
Yes, whatever you need.
Just say the word, sir.

318
00:22:12,122 --> 00:22:16,668
I'd like to find out if there have been
any shareholding changes

319
00:22:16,752 --> 00:22:19,921
among Hanmin executives
or anyone in the chairman's inner circle.

320
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:23,133
Gosh, sir. Are you already…

321
00:22:23,717 --> 00:22:25,302
that well-informed?

322
00:22:27,012 --> 00:22:28,764
Who else knows about this?

323
00:22:28,847 --> 00:22:30,223
Ms. Song Ju-ran…

324
00:22:33,435 --> 00:22:37,606
Walk me through
exactly what you reported to her.

325
00:22:38,648 --> 00:22:41,318
Darn it, this big mouth of mine…

326
00:22:46,573 --> 00:22:47,783
Hold on.

327
00:22:51,495 --> 00:22:55,499
Executive Director Oh Deok-gyu
disposed of his entire holding

328
00:22:55,582 --> 00:22:57,250
except for one share.

329
00:22:57,834 --> 00:22:59,753
It comes to nearly 9%.

330
00:23:00,837 --> 00:23:01,671
And this is something…

331
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:05,634
that I didn't even disclose to Ms. Song.

332
00:23:06,551 --> 00:23:10,597
I finally uncovered the buyer's name.

333
00:23:11,139 --> 00:23:12,224
Who is it?

334
00:23:15,602 --> 00:23:17,437
It's a name you would've heard of as well.

335
00:23:18,814 --> 00:23:20,232
Right, so who is it?

336
00:23:23,693 --> 00:23:25,112
Yeouido Pirates.

337
00:23:26,113 --> 00:23:27,739
I even found out the name of its CEO.

338
00:23:29,407 --> 00:23:31,284
"Hong Keum-bo."

339
00:23:36,248 --> 00:23:37,666
Before you joined us, Mr. Shin,

340
00:23:37,749 --> 00:23:40,710
the prosecutors probed into
Hanmin's slush fund,

341
00:23:40,794 --> 00:23:43,880
and one of the FSS members involved then
was named Hong Keum-bo.

342
00:23:43,964 --> 00:23:45,632
It could be just a namesake,

343
00:23:45,715 --> 00:23:47,509
but it's not a common name, you know?

344
00:23:47,592 --> 00:23:49,344
Hong Keum-bo is rather rare, isn't it?

345
00:23:49,427 --> 00:23:51,680
Thank you. That will do.

346
00:23:51,763 --> 00:23:52,597
You may leave.

347
00:23:53,181 --> 00:23:54,266
Oh, already?

348
00:24:05,485 --> 00:24:06,570
Sir.

349
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:10,198
The short-term bonds mature
next Wednesday.

350
00:24:11,658 --> 00:24:15,787
President Shin, DK Ventures will be able
to assist us again this time, right?

351
00:24:16,496 --> 00:24:18,999
Yes, I'll let them know in advance.

352
00:24:19,082 --> 00:24:20,750
No, there's no need.

353
00:24:20,834 --> 00:24:23,587
That will be unnecessary this time.

354
00:24:23,670 --> 00:24:25,463
I'm planning to tap into the reserves

355
00:24:25,547 --> 00:24:28,633
set aside for employee wages
and severance pay.

356
00:24:28,717 --> 00:24:30,385
You can't do that, sir.

357
00:24:30,468 --> 00:24:34,014
The restructuring has already strained
internal sentiment and working conditions,

358
00:24:34,598 --> 00:24:36,266
so that may accelerate staff turnover.

359
00:24:36,349 --> 00:24:38,310
That's exactly what I'm after.

360
00:24:38,852 --> 00:24:40,437
When the company is struggling,

361
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:43,440
the employees should share
some of the burden.

362
00:24:44,441 --> 00:24:45,609
Also,

363
00:24:45,692 --> 00:24:48,069
I heard this at one of my gatherings.

364
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:51,489
There are rumors going around

365
00:24:52,073 --> 00:24:54,117
that the CEO of DK Ventures…

366
00:24:55,785 --> 00:24:59,164
has been staying in Korea
and shopping around for companies.

367
00:25:01,791 --> 00:25:04,461
Given the undervaluation
of the Korean stock market,

368
00:25:04,544 --> 00:25:06,171
I believe he's considering investments.

369
00:25:08,632 --> 00:25:09,466
Is that so?

370
00:25:28,568 --> 00:25:29,527
What is it?

371
00:25:29,611 --> 00:25:32,030
You were the moderator of Yeouido Pirates?

372
00:25:32,739 --> 00:25:33,573
No.

373
00:25:33,657 --> 00:25:35,408
Yeouido Pirates is buying up
Hanmin stocks,

374
00:25:35,492 --> 00:25:37,077
and Hong Keum-bo is listed as its CEO.

375
00:25:37,869 --> 00:25:39,412
Yeah, that part is true.

376
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:44,000
Why did you buy up Oh Deok-gyu's shares?

377
00:25:44,084 --> 00:25:44,918
Was a deal struck?

378
00:25:46,628 --> 00:25:49,881
As if he'd ever be willing
to make a deal with me.

379
00:25:49,965 --> 00:25:51,549
So you just swooped in then.

380
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:52,592
What are you up to?

381
00:25:54,135 --> 00:25:58,306
I'm stopping Shin Jung-woo and DK Ventures
from destroying Hanmin.

382
00:25:58,390 --> 00:25:59,557
That's what I'm up to.

383
00:26:00,141 --> 00:26:01,226
Let's get one thing straight.

384
00:26:01,309 --> 00:26:03,395
It was already in ruins
before I ever got here.

385
00:26:03,478 --> 00:26:06,064
Just look at how Chairman Kang
manages his own company.

386
00:26:07,816 --> 00:26:08,650
Forget it.

387
00:26:09,567 --> 00:26:13,947
You're not trying to acquire shares
to seize Hanmin, right?

388
00:26:15,323 --> 00:26:17,784
Am I not allowed to have
the same aspirations?

389
00:26:19,411 --> 00:26:22,914
You're also putting on this act
while praying for Hanmin to fall.

390
00:26:28,128 --> 00:26:29,296
Should we make a bet?

391
00:26:30,213 --> 00:26:32,173
Between Hong Keum-bo and Shin Jung-woo,

392
00:26:32,257 --> 00:26:34,259
who do you think
will be kicked out of Hanmin first?

393
00:26:36,219 --> 00:26:37,762
I'll bet on you.

394
00:26:51,693 --> 00:26:53,320
I hope there are no misunderstandings.

395
00:26:53,403 --> 00:26:55,447
There won't be.

396
00:26:55,530 --> 00:26:57,198
I just heard everything.

397
00:26:57,907 --> 00:26:59,576
You summoned me, so you explain.

398
00:27:22,098 --> 00:27:24,642
When I saw the news about
President Kang's accident in July,

399
00:27:24,726 --> 00:27:26,770
I was the one
who reached out to the chairman

400
00:27:26,853 --> 00:27:28,772
and expressed interest in joining Hanmin.

401
00:27:28,855 --> 00:27:31,066
But earlier, Ms. Hong said

402
00:27:31,149 --> 00:27:35,320
that you and DK Ventures
were looking to destroy Hanmin.

403
00:27:36,029 --> 00:27:37,739
That's what I heard.

404
00:27:38,239 --> 00:27:39,991
That's a difference of opinion.

405
00:27:41,076 --> 00:27:43,870
I assume you refer to her as "Ms. Hong"

406
00:27:43,953 --> 00:27:47,123
because you found out
she's Hong Keum-bo and not Hong Jang-mi?

407
00:27:47,916 --> 00:27:49,918
Yes, but I can't tell you any more.

408
00:27:50,001 --> 00:27:51,503
I'm pretty loyal, you see.

409
00:27:52,837 --> 00:27:55,757
If people find out the lead investigator
on the slush fund probe

410
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:57,842
infiltrated the company undercover,

411
00:27:58,593 --> 00:28:00,220
she could be in danger.

412
00:28:02,097 --> 00:28:04,099
It's all Kang Pil-beom's money anyway.

413
00:28:04,182 --> 00:28:06,351
Do you know how he made all that money?

414
00:28:06,434 --> 00:28:09,062
That's why she got so angry that time.

415
00:28:10,105 --> 00:28:12,357
Money, slush fund…

416
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:14,776
That's why I pulled her aside
and tried to persuade her today.

417
00:28:16,444 --> 00:28:18,738
I'll make sure Keum-bo returns safely.

418
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:23,034
Because you still have feelings for her?

419
00:28:27,288 --> 00:28:29,541
The last person my brother called…

420
00:28:31,501 --> 00:28:32,377
was me.

421
00:28:34,170 --> 00:28:35,171
When he did,

422
00:28:35,922 --> 00:28:38,466
I hounded him, scolded him,

423
00:28:40,051 --> 00:28:41,803
and told him he was naive.

424
00:28:42,762 --> 00:28:44,597
I yelled and cursed him out.

425
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:48,977
A part of me was worried about him,
but the truth is,

426
00:28:49,060 --> 00:28:50,520
I was worried it could hurt me.

427
00:28:51,688 --> 00:28:53,314
I was more worried about myself.

428
00:28:54,858 --> 00:28:56,693
It became a lasting regret.

429
00:28:57,652 --> 00:28:59,028
You must have

430
00:28:59,654 --> 00:29:01,406
similar regret.

431
00:29:02,031 --> 00:29:04,159
What does clinging to that
so-called conscience get you?

432
00:29:04,242 --> 00:29:06,369
It's not about gains.
It's about not losing it!

433
00:29:07,912 --> 00:29:10,540
And is whatever you gain worth losing me?

434
00:29:13,084 --> 00:29:13,960
No.

435
00:29:16,045 --> 00:29:17,672
I just don't want another regret.

436
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:40,945
I only followed you there yesterday
to ask about our dinner plans.

437
00:29:41,029 --> 00:29:42,447
I wasn't tailing you or anything.

438
00:29:43,698 --> 00:29:44,699
I understand.

439
00:29:45,950 --> 00:29:49,454
But the fact that you and Bok-hee
are hiding stuff from me

440
00:29:49,537 --> 00:29:50,830
makes me a bit sad.

441
00:29:54,751 --> 00:29:57,212
It's because we can't keep
asking you for help,

442
00:29:57,295 --> 00:29:59,172
and we don't want to
take advantage of you.

443
00:29:59,714 --> 00:30:00,548
After all,

444
00:30:01,841 --> 00:30:03,384
you're a part of Chairman Kang's family.

445
00:30:06,471 --> 00:30:07,972
The slush fund probe?

446
00:30:09,474 --> 00:30:11,059
Who told you about that?

447
00:30:11,142 --> 00:30:13,061
President Shin told me yesterday.

448
00:30:16,231 --> 00:30:18,024
That man is so damn useless.

449
00:30:20,777 --> 00:30:23,571
I'll keep it a secret.

450
00:30:23,655 --> 00:30:26,574
I won't do anything
that would put everyone in danger.

451
00:30:26,658 --> 00:30:27,492
Don't worry.

452
00:30:48,429 --> 00:30:49,472
Truth be told,

453
00:30:50,390 --> 00:30:53,476
I have no reason to show you this
before anyone else.

454
00:30:54,060 --> 00:30:56,354
But we're going to be family soon,

455
00:30:56,437 --> 00:30:58,982
and we'll both be sons-in-law. Here.

456
00:30:59,983 --> 00:31:01,818
Last time, with K…

457
00:31:01,901 --> 00:31:03,236
I mean, take a look.

458
00:31:03,987 --> 00:31:05,405
<i>This will be my safety net.</i>

459
00:31:05,905 --> 00:31:08,491
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES
SECOND-ROUND RESTRUCTURING LIST

460
00:31:14,706 --> 00:31:16,249
Can I add someone to this list?

461
00:31:16,332 --> 00:31:17,834
What? Who?

462
00:31:17,917 --> 00:31:21,129
There was that female employee who was
almost fired after the order-entry error.

463
00:31:22,589 --> 00:31:25,800
We had to tread lightly and be mindful
of public opinion back then, but now…

464
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:28,094
Right, this would be the ideal time.

465
00:31:28,177 --> 00:31:29,846
In fact, there was an article

466
00:31:29,929 --> 00:31:33,683
about "voluntary restructuring"
in the politics section of today's paper.

467
00:31:33,766 --> 00:31:36,811
That's actually
the administration sending a signal.

468
00:31:36,895 --> 00:31:39,772
We should take this chance
to clear out the troublemakers

469
00:31:39,856 --> 00:31:41,608
and the deadweight.

470
00:31:42,275 --> 00:31:44,110
Regarding funds…

471
00:31:44,193 --> 00:31:46,154
Never mind. Write down the name.

472
00:31:48,948 --> 00:31:54,120
HONG JANG-MI

473
00:32:05,214 --> 00:32:07,592
It's customary for female staff decisions
to go through me.

474
00:32:08,843 --> 00:32:11,387
Please postpone
the second round of restructuring.

475
00:32:12,263 --> 00:32:14,557
We should revisit it
after I conduct a thorough review--

476
00:32:14,641 --> 00:32:17,060
And what if I disagree with that custom?

477
00:32:18,186 --> 00:32:20,688
A chief of staff
controlling HR at a company

478
00:32:20,772 --> 00:32:22,815
and only for one gender at that?

479
00:32:23,483 --> 00:32:24,609
Since when has this been the norm?

480
00:32:26,527 --> 00:32:28,780
That's not a custom
but an abuse of authority.

481
00:32:30,031 --> 00:32:31,699
Follow your superior's directive.

482
00:32:32,325 --> 00:32:33,534
You may leave.

483
00:32:51,219 --> 00:32:53,054
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES
SECOND-ROUND RESTRUCTURING LIST

484
00:32:56,015 --> 00:32:57,767
RESEARCH DIVISION: HONG JANG-MI

485
00:32:59,102 --> 00:33:00,436
Well done, Mr. Oh.

486
00:33:01,187 --> 00:33:02,814
Have you reviewed it, Mr. Shin?

487
00:33:02,897 --> 00:33:04,232
Yes, sir. I have no objections.

488
00:33:04,315 --> 00:33:05,149
Good.

489
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:06,776
Let's see here.

490
00:33:06,859 --> 00:33:08,027
Sir.

491
00:33:09,445 --> 00:33:11,447
I haven't had the chance to review it.

492
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,659
Could you perhaps delay
the final decision a bit, sir?

493
00:33:15,994 --> 00:33:18,830
I had Executive Director Oh
take care of it for a reason.

494
00:33:18,913 --> 00:33:23,126
You already have your hands full
with Nora's wedding preparations.

495
00:33:24,127 --> 00:33:27,005
With the Lunar New Year holiday coming up,
it'd be better to proceed now.

496
00:33:27,088 --> 00:33:30,258
Given her involvement
in the order-entry incident,

497
00:33:30,758 --> 00:33:32,885
Ms. Hong Jang-mi
poses a risk of internal discord.

498
00:33:32,969 --> 00:33:36,014
But she was
the Outstanding Woman last quarter.

499
00:33:36,931 --> 00:33:39,642
Imagine what everyone would say
about our performance review system

500
00:33:39,726 --> 00:33:41,894
if we terminated an employee
who was just honored.

501
00:33:41,978 --> 00:33:43,104
That's enough.

502
00:33:43,187 --> 00:33:47,567
Is it worth all this fuss
over just one female employee?

503
00:33:47,650 --> 00:33:50,361
Perhaps we can just
keep her on the payroll

504
00:33:50,945 --> 00:33:53,322
and tuck her away somewhere out of sight?

505
00:33:59,954 --> 00:34:01,831
How can they just spring this on us?

506
00:34:02,540 --> 00:34:05,084
They never post stuff like this
on the intranet.

507
00:34:10,465 --> 00:34:11,424
Ms. Hong.

508
00:34:11,507 --> 00:34:13,176
I'm not the least bit surprised.

509
00:34:13,676 --> 00:34:15,970
It's time you faced
society's bitter realities.

510
00:34:16,804 --> 00:34:18,890
You should be grateful
they didn't just fire you.

511
00:34:19,766 --> 00:34:22,852
Mr. Cha, you should also read
the announcement below.

512
00:34:24,937 --> 00:34:27,648
DEPUTY MANAGERS AND ABOVE WILL RECEIVE
THEIR JANUARY SALARY IN FEBRUARY

513
00:34:27,732 --> 00:34:29,525
We're not getting paid this month?

514
00:34:29,609 --> 00:34:32,570
The bitter realities of society
don't discriminate by status.

515
00:34:33,071 --> 00:34:34,947
You're not exempt either.

516
00:34:49,337 --> 00:34:50,838
DEPUTY MANAGERS AND ABOVE WILL RECEIVE
THEIR JANUARY SALARY IN FEBRUARY

517
00:34:59,305 --> 00:35:01,307
Deputy managers and above
are going to be paid late.

518
00:35:02,308 --> 00:35:04,811
Man, I should've left with you back then.

519
00:35:05,895 --> 00:35:08,940
Don't say things you don't mean.
Just hang in there, no matter what.

520
00:35:09,607 --> 00:35:10,858
Let's drink tonight.

521
00:35:11,442 --> 00:35:13,319
I can't, I'm…

522
00:35:15,530 --> 00:35:16,614
I have plans.

523
00:35:16,697 --> 00:35:17,907
Let's talk later.

524
00:35:17,990 --> 00:35:18,866
I'll call you.

525
00:35:19,659 --> 00:35:21,702
All right. Just hang up already.

526
00:35:22,703 --> 00:35:23,538
Bang…

527
00:35:46,769 --> 00:35:49,730
1998 EXPERIENCED CANDIDATES INTERVIEW

528
00:35:54,861 --> 00:35:55,987
Mr. Bang Jin-mok?

529
00:35:56,070 --> 00:35:57,488
Yes. Here.

530
00:36:02,285 --> 00:36:03,494
SINYONG BANK
HONG KEUM-BO, ACCOUNT HISTORY

531
00:36:03,578 --> 00:36:04,579
JOGEOK BANK
HONG KEUM-BO, ACCOUNT HISTORY

532
00:36:08,124 --> 00:36:09,458
ACCOUNT HOLDER: HONG JANG-MI

533
00:36:11,335 --> 00:36:14,172
ACCOUNT HISTORY
ACCOUNT HOLDER: GO BOK-HEE

534
00:36:16,883 --> 00:36:18,801
Hong Keum-bo, Hong Jang-mi,
and even Go Bok-hee.

535
00:36:19,552 --> 00:36:20,845
None of them have
such transaction records.

536
00:36:20,928 --> 00:36:25,099
Could they have used
a borrowed-name account?

537
00:36:25,766 --> 00:36:26,684
No.

538
00:36:27,894 --> 00:36:29,520
I tracked the checks,

539
00:36:29,604 --> 00:36:31,480
and they were cashed out by someone else.

540
00:36:32,481 --> 00:36:33,691
They've already exchanged them.

541
00:36:34,525 --> 00:36:36,194
They have the money in cash.

542
00:36:37,486 --> 00:36:39,864
I can't beat her down,
and I can't kick her to the curb.

543
00:36:39,947 --> 00:36:43,826
I had Go Bok-cheol tail Hong Keum-bo.

544
00:36:44,327 --> 00:36:48,831
But she only ever goes to her apartment,
the office, and the dorms.

545
00:36:50,958 --> 00:36:51,918
It's in the dorm.

546
00:36:54,378 --> 00:36:56,172
Start by searching Room 301.

547
00:37:02,470 --> 00:37:03,346
SEOUL CITY DORMITORY
FOR SINGLE FEMALE WORKERS

548
00:37:03,429 --> 00:37:06,057
It might've started out
as Hong Keum-bo's personal objective,

549
00:37:06,140 --> 00:37:07,141
but not anymore.

550
00:37:07,225 --> 00:37:09,644
You're in the driver's seat, so drive.

551
00:37:09,727 --> 00:37:11,979
Why aren't you doing anything
with the money?

552
00:37:12,647 --> 00:37:15,858
I want to take care of Shin Jung-woo first
before I make my move.

553
00:37:16,525 --> 00:37:20,071
One by one, we need to take out anyone
Chairman Kang trusts enough

554
00:37:20,738 --> 00:37:23,241
to use against us
when he finds out about our plan.

555
00:37:23,741 --> 00:37:25,660
Shin Jung-woo is the first target.

556
00:37:26,702 --> 00:37:28,246
ELIMINATING CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM'S
INNER CIRCLE

557
00:37:28,329 --> 00:37:30,289
ALBERT OH: ON OUR SIDE
KANG NORA: ?

558
00:37:30,373 --> 00:37:31,624
STEP 1: PRESIDENT SHIN JUNG-WOO

559
00:37:32,583 --> 00:37:35,962
I'm surprised you're not suggesting
that we flee with the money.

560
00:37:37,296 --> 00:37:38,464
Don't be so sure I won't.

561
00:39:07,928 --> 00:39:09,889
- Jang-mi.
- I'm fine, so get out of here.

562
00:39:09,972 --> 00:39:10,931
Now!

563
00:39:13,267 --> 00:39:14,268
But Bom,

564
00:39:14,852 --> 00:39:16,979
I'll hold onto this
because it's dangerous.

565
00:39:22,818 --> 00:39:23,819
No, wait. Stop.

566
00:39:23,903 --> 00:39:25,237
Get out of here quietly,

567
00:39:25,321 --> 00:39:26,864
or I'll burn all this money!

568
00:39:30,493 --> 00:39:31,827
Help!

569
00:39:42,671 --> 00:39:43,839
- What's going on?
- What's happening?

570
00:39:43,923 --> 00:39:45,174
Is there a fire in Room 301?

571
00:39:45,257 --> 00:39:46,258
It's a burglar!

572
00:39:46,342 --> 00:39:47,510
We've got a burglar!

573
00:39:52,598 --> 00:39:53,682
Damn it.

574
00:40:11,325 --> 00:40:12,201
Damn it.

575
00:40:12,743 --> 00:40:14,161
How dare you break in here?

576
00:40:14,245 --> 00:40:15,704
- What's this now?
- Stop right there!

577
00:40:16,414 --> 00:40:17,623
Stop!

578
00:40:20,918 --> 00:40:22,920
- You punk!
- Stop right there!

579
00:40:32,555 --> 00:40:33,389
You bastard!

580
00:40:35,266 --> 00:40:36,100
Where did he go?

581
00:40:37,101 --> 00:40:38,185
Where did that punk go?

582
00:40:39,145 --> 00:40:40,062
- That bastard.
- What was that?

583
00:40:49,405 --> 00:40:51,365
Jang-mi, open this door!

584
00:40:54,285 --> 00:40:55,911
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere?

585
00:40:55,995 --> 00:40:58,038
Did you set off the fire alarm?

586
00:40:58,122 --> 00:40:59,373
Tell me you're okay first!

587
00:40:59,457 --> 00:41:00,708
I'm fine.

588
00:41:00,791 --> 00:41:03,002
He ran off
as soon as the fire alarm went off.

589
00:41:09,216 --> 00:41:11,635
I thought you'd be worried
about the money,

590
00:41:11,719 --> 00:41:13,387
but you worried about me first.

591
00:41:13,471 --> 00:41:14,722
Seriously?

592
00:41:14,805 --> 00:41:18,267
I may be crazy about money,
but of course I'd save you first!

593
00:41:18,350 --> 00:41:20,811
Do you really think I'd run away
just to save myself?

594
00:41:24,273 --> 00:41:25,149
It's okay.

595
00:41:25,649 --> 00:41:26,984
I hate you!

596
00:41:35,784 --> 00:41:37,203
I wasn't able to catch the burglar.

597
00:41:37,286 --> 00:41:38,287
Are you two all right?

598
00:41:39,205 --> 00:41:40,080
Is there anything missing?

599
00:41:40,581 --> 00:41:41,790
I'll go to your room now--

600
00:41:41,874 --> 00:41:43,626
- It's okay.
- Nothing is missing.

601
00:41:45,211 --> 00:41:46,420
I reported it to the police.

602
00:41:47,004 --> 00:41:48,797
They said they'll reinforce patrol units,

603
00:41:48,881 --> 00:41:51,133
but please be sure to lock your doors.

604
00:41:51,926 --> 00:41:52,843
Thank you.

605
00:41:58,766 --> 00:42:01,685
I recognized his face.

606
00:42:02,478 --> 00:42:03,395
What?

607
00:42:03,479 --> 00:42:05,773
I was almost kidnapped once
before I moved in here,

608
00:42:06,565 --> 00:42:08,609
and he was the man
driving the van back then.

609
00:42:09,652 --> 00:42:12,279
He was also involved in
Kang Myeong-hwi's accident.

610
00:42:14,198 --> 00:42:15,616
Ms. Song must've sent him, right?

611
00:42:17,368 --> 00:42:18,410
Probably.

612
00:42:25,042 --> 00:42:28,254
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

613
00:42:38,806 --> 00:42:40,224
What are you doing here
at the head office?

614
00:42:41,350 --> 00:42:42,560
You were transferred.

615
00:42:42,643 --> 00:42:45,396
After the first restructuring
last December,

616
00:42:45,479 --> 00:42:48,857
the female employees signed a separate,
additional employment contract.

617
00:42:52,570 --> 00:42:54,238
See right there? A one-year contract.

618
00:42:54,321 --> 00:42:55,155
EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT

619
00:42:55,781 --> 00:42:57,908
Ordering a transfer to a remote region

620
00:42:57,992 --> 00:43:00,494
with no personal ties
and without a valid reason

621
00:43:00,578 --> 00:43:02,621
is clearly an unjust personnel action.

622
00:43:03,831 --> 00:43:06,333
You should be complaining about this
to President Shin, not me.

623
00:43:07,710 --> 00:43:10,087
That would be the end
of Hong Jang-mi's complaint.

624
00:43:11,297 --> 00:43:12,881
Now, we'll move on to Hong Keum-bo's.

625
00:43:15,092 --> 00:43:17,970
You attempted
quite an ambitious stunt last night.

626
00:43:18,053 --> 00:43:20,598
I assume Mr. Auto Repair Shop
reported back?

627
00:43:21,223 --> 00:43:23,350
You hid all that money in a dorm room?

628
00:43:25,394 --> 00:43:26,937
Now that you've confirmed that,

629
00:43:27,479 --> 00:43:29,690
you just have to make a decision.

630
00:43:31,233 --> 00:43:35,279
I believe our deal remains on the table.

631
00:43:44,538 --> 00:43:47,207
<i>In the meantime,</i>
<i>we'll quietly accumulate more bonds.</i>

632
00:43:48,542 --> 00:43:50,753
And if Hanmin goes bankrupt on its own?
That's a win for us.

633
00:43:51,337 --> 00:43:52,671
If he continues to hold out,

634
00:43:52,755 --> 00:43:55,799
we'll take over Hanmin
with a surprise court receivership filing

635
00:43:56,383 --> 00:43:58,427
and spruce it up to sell it.

636
00:43:58,510 --> 00:43:59,511
Then

637
00:43:59,595 --> 00:44:01,639
<i>all of Yeouido</i>
<i>will be in the palm of our hands.</i>

638
00:44:03,974 --> 00:44:07,936
DK Ventures has already been in contact
with other Korean companies.

639
00:44:09,355 --> 00:44:12,608
I'm sure they'll try to avoid the fallout
of their investment plans

640
00:44:12,691 --> 00:44:15,235
by cutting Shin Jung-woo loose.

641
00:44:25,454 --> 00:44:27,331
If Hanmin ends up in their hands,

642
00:44:27,414 --> 00:44:29,583
the 12th floor will be the first
to get wiped out.

643
00:44:30,751 --> 00:44:33,754
Do you want to be kicked out
after running errands for 30 years?

644
00:44:37,966 --> 00:44:41,470
Are you sure your personal grudge
against him isn't clouding your judgment?

645
00:44:43,055 --> 00:44:44,556
I see you've done some digging.

646
00:44:45,474 --> 00:44:46,684
A university alum,

647
00:44:47,351 --> 00:44:49,645
co-workers at your first job as a CPA,

648
00:44:50,479 --> 00:44:52,022
and ex-lovers.

649
00:44:53,023 --> 00:44:55,150
You two were passionate in your twenties.

650
00:44:57,319 --> 00:45:00,948
You can choose whichever card works best,

651
00:45:01,448 --> 00:45:02,699
then play it with Chairman Kang.

652
00:45:03,450 --> 00:45:04,576
I couldn't care less.

653
00:45:29,309 --> 00:45:30,894
Why those punks…

654
00:45:31,687 --> 00:45:33,272
They have the audacity

655
00:45:33,355 --> 00:45:36,066
to eye my company with mere chump change?

656
00:45:36,150 --> 00:45:39,236
Ms. Kang and President Shin's
engagement party is tomorrow.

657
00:45:40,112 --> 00:45:42,072
We need to act quickly.

658
00:45:42,906 --> 00:45:44,616
You know,

659
00:45:44,700 --> 00:45:51,665
if DK Ventures floods the market
with all the Hanmin bonds they have,

660
00:45:52,207 --> 00:45:54,918
then we will be helpless.

661
00:45:55,002 --> 00:45:56,753
Us failing to secure the public funds

662
00:45:56,837 --> 00:46:00,132
was a part of Shin Jung-woo's plan
to set the stage for DK Ventures.

663
00:46:00,841 --> 00:46:01,967
You're right.

664
00:46:02,759 --> 00:46:05,262
I only let him off the hook for that

665
00:46:05,345 --> 00:46:07,389
because he secured the funds immediately.

666
00:46:08,515 --> 00:46:10,142
As you are already aware,

667
00:46:10,726 --> 00:46:14,855
DK Ventures is actively investing
in other Korean companies as well.

668
00:46:15,647 --> 00:46:17,149
I'm sure the CEO would rather

669
00:46:17,733 --> 00:46:20,235
cut Shin Jung-woo than take major losses.

670
00:46:22,154 --> 00:46:25,407
I will meet with him tomorrow

671
00:46:25,491 --> 00:46:27,618
and confirm it myself.

672
00:46:33,290 --> 00:46:36,168
A hostile takeover?
You've misunderstood, sir.

673
00:46:36,752 --> 00:46:38,545
Hanmin was the one who suggested

674
00:46:38,629 --> 00:46:40,214
the issuance of bonds over an investment.

675
00:46:40,297 --> 00:46:41,340
No.

676
00:46:41,423 --> 00:46:42,674
To be exact,

677
00:46:43,509 --> 00:46:45,594
that was Shin Jung-woo's suggestion.

678
00:46:46,887 --> 00:46:51,141
Why would the infiltrator
planted by DK Ventures

679
00:46:51,975 --> 00:46:54,061
ever work for me, huh?

680
00:46:54,144 --> 00:46:55,771
That's pure speculation.

681
00:46:56,355 --> 00:46:59,107
Why don't you invite President Shin
and ask him yourself?

682
00:46:59,191 --> 00:47:02,277
The original intent
may have been questionable,

683
00:47:03,111 --> 00:47:05,197
but the result is what counts.

684
00:47:06,031 --> 00:47:06,907
I, for one,

685
00:47:06,990 --> 00:47:11,495
do not wish to ruin
my relationship with DK Ventures.

686
00:47:14,873 --> 00:47:18,293
I'm trying to tell you
that everything will be settled

687
00:47:18,377 --> 00:47:19,586
if we handle one person.

688
00:47:21,547 --> 00:47:23,715
<i>…and spruce it up to sell it.</i>

689
00:47:23,799 --> 00:47:26,635
<i>Then all of Yeouido</i>
<i>will be in the palm of our hands.</i>

690
00:47:29,638 --> 00:47:32,975
Have you been recording
every conversation in my office like this?

691
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:35,727
That's not what's important.

692
00:47:37,938 --> 00:47:41,191
Leave the company quietly.

693
00:47:41,275 --> 00:47:42,943
That is the chairman's wish.

694
00:47:43,026 --> 00:47:44,945
And why would I take orders from you?

695
00:47:46,238 --> 00:47:47,531
At least

696
00:47:48,448 --> 00:47:52,202
I didn't disclose to the chairman
what I know about Hong Keum-bo.

697
00:47:52,286 --> 00:47:54,079
You must be saving it for leverage later!

698
00:47:58,458 --> 00:48:00,919
I will speak to the chairman myself.

699
00:48:12,347 --> 00:48:15,726
LIST OF KOREAN COMPANIES, 1998

700
00:48:16,393 --> 00:48:17,269
Here.

701
00:48:19,187 --> 00:48:20,188
Does that look familiar?

702
00:48:21,148 --> 00:48:25,819
It's the list of Korean companies
DK Ventures approached

703
00:48:25,902 --> 00:48:28,322
using their shell company.

704
00:48:28,405 --> 00:48:32,826
You call yourself a venture firm,
claiming to back startups.

705
00:48:33,410 --> 00:48:35,662
But every company
you targeted overseas was

706
00:48:36,288 --> 00:48:38,707
a solid mid-sized corporation.

707
00:48:39,541 --> 00:48:42,127
Did you really think
I'd enter into business with someone

708
00:48:42,210 --> 00:48:44,379
without doing due diligence?

709
00:48:45,130 --> 00:48:48,967
I may not be able to make you prosper,
but I can certainly ruin you.

710
00:48:49,468 --> 00:48:52,596
I can make sure
your Korean investments go up in smoke

711
00:48:53,180 --> 00:48:55,682
and shut you out
of the Korean market for good.

712
00:48:55,766 --> 00:48:56,683
Sir.

713
00:48:56,767 --> 00:48:58,018
Thanks to you,

714
00:48:58,101 --> 00:49:02,064
I'll be painted as the patriotic old guard
who fought off foreign capital

715
00:49:02,939 --> 00:49:04,816
to save his company

716
00:49:05,817 --> 00:49:10,238
and shield other Korean firms
from being devoured.

717
00:49:14,618 --> 00:49:17,329
If we just push out Shin Jung-woo,

718
00:49:17,412 --> 00:49:20,957
we could all maintain peace.

719
00:49:22,918 --> 00:49:26,838
You only have
the company's fate on the line,

720
00:49:27,673 --> 00:49:28,548
but for me…

721
00:49:30,217 --> 00:49:34,304
my daughter's engagement is also at stake.

722
00:49:46,233 --> 00:49:48,568
I will comply with your wishes.

723
00:49:50,362 --> 00:49:51,613
Good!

724
00:49:51,697 --> 00:49:52,656
All right!

725
00:49:53,407 --> 00:49:54,366
It's settled.

726
00:49:54,950 --> 00:49:56,076
Well done.

727
00:50:10,424 --> 00:50:11,508
All right then.

728
00:50:43,290 --> 00:50:44,124
Take a seat.

729
00:50:49,713 --> 00:50:53,550
We have three hours
until the engagement party.

730
00:51:03,018 --> 00:51:05,061
CONGRATULATIONS ON YOUR ENGAGEMENT

731
00:51:21,369 --> 00:51:22,496
Hold on.

732
00:51:24,372 --> 00:51:25,832
Is this someone's 60th birthday party?

733
00:51:26,416 --> 00:51:27,501
Get rid of anything drab.

734
00:51:29,002 --> 00:51:30,045
Take it away.

735
00:51:31,963 --> 00:51:33,423
Welcome, sir.

736
00:51:33,507 --> 00:51:34,466
Hey.

737
00:51:36,384 --> 00:51:37,511
Honey.

738
00:51:40,680 --> 00:51:42,182
Not that way.

739
00:51:42,265 --> 00:51:43,391
Move it.

740
00:51:43,475 --> 00:51:45,352
- It's this way.
- Goodness.

741
00:51:45,435 --> 00:51:49,231
Isn't it better to take
the commemorative shots at the end?

742
00:51:49,314 --> 00:51:52,526
Come on, this is supposed to be
a cozy family affair.

743
00:51:52,609 --> 00:51:54,778
- Gosh.
- We should take lots of family shots.

744
00:52:01,535 --> 00:52:02,953
Smile.

745
00:52:04,120 --> 00:52:05,997
Look at all this unnecessary fuss.

746
00:52:06,498 --> 00:52:09,417
Let's make sure yours is a simple,
sophisticated affair.

747
00:52:10,669 --> 00:52:11,503
Sure.

748
00:52:13,588 --> 00:52:15,674
We're still missing
the stars of today's show.

749
00:52:26,142 --> 00:52:28,937
CELEBRATING THE ENGAGEMENT
OF SHIN JUNG-WOO AND KANG NORA

750
00:52:48,999 --> 00:52:49,916
<i>Nora.</i>

751
00:52:51,543 --> 00:52:52,794
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

752
00:52:53,378 --> 00:52:56,548
I don't think
I'll be able to make it today.

753
00:53:02,679 --> 00:53:04,472
Do other people know?

754
00:53:06,850 --> 00:53:07,726
No.

755
00:53:13,189 --> 00:53:14,149
Nora!

756
00:53:15,191 --> 00:53:16,234
Nora!

757
00:53:16,318 --> 00:53:17,777
Where did she go?

758
00:53:21,031 --> 00:53:22,449
Oh my. Nora.

759
00:53:23,658 --> 00:53:24,534
Nora.

760
00:53:27,913 --> 00:53:30,081
Nora, why did you lock the doors?

761
00:53:30,165 --> 00:53:32,792
You only have five minutes left.

762
00:53:32,876 --> 00:53:34,502
Who are you on the phone with?

763
00:53:35,462 --> 00:53:36,296
Then…

764
00:53:37,172 --> 00:53:38,924
can you tell them I dumped you?

765
00:53:40,300 --> 00:53:42,344
Tell them I called off the engagement.

766
00:53:46,973 --> 00:53:47,891
Nora.

767
00:54:00,695 --> 00:54:01,738
Why are you crying?

768
00:54:02,238 --> 00:54:03,156
Nora.

769
00:54:37,816 --> 00:54:39,359
Something's not right.

770
00:54:40,360 --> 00:54:41,403
Why aren't they starting?

771
00:54:43,113 --> 00:54:45,323
Maybe something happened?

772
00:54:46,783 --> 00:54:48,618
Are they still not here?

773
00:54:48,702 --> 00:54:50,161
The chairman's there.

774
00:54:50,245 --> 00:54:51,496
What is going on?

775
00:54:51,579 --> 00:54:53,081
They're still not here.

776
00:55:13,685 --> 00:55:14,686
I'm sorry.

777
00:55:16,730 --> 00:55:17,897
You're sorry?

778
00:55:18,398 --> 00:55:21,067
President Shin, are you out of your mind?

779
00:55:21,609 --> 00:55:23,778
How could you humiliate us like this?

780
00:55:25,155 --> 00:55:26,114
My Nora.

781
00:55:26,197 --> 00:55:27,866
What are you going to do about my Nora?

782
00:55:27,949 --> 00:55:29,409
Tell me!

783
00:55:41,254 --> 00:55:43,006
<i>So, what will you do?</i>

784
00:55:43,089 --> 00:55:47,052
We can carry on
with the engagement party as planned.

785
00:55:48,178 --> 00:55:50,221
Both Nora and her mother

786
00:55:50,972 --> 00:55:52,974
are excited about the princess play,

787
00:55:53,892 --> 00:55:56,436
so we can't disappoint them.

788
00:55:57,020 --> 00:55:59,022
A mere scandal of a broken engagement

789
00:55:59,939 --> 00:56:02,400
will be forgotten over time.

790
00:56:03,735 --> 00:56:05,945
If you care about Nora as her father,

791
00:56:06,988 --> 00:56:08,323
you should call it off now.

792
00:56:09,115 --> 00:56:10,033
Is that so?

793
00:56:11,868 --> 00:56:13,703
Then let's do that.

794
00:56:15,080 --> 00:56:16,998
Let's make one thing clear.

795
00:56:18,083 --> 00:56:19,542
You're the one who called it off.

796
00:56:20,710 --> 00:56:23,421
I, too, do not wish

797
00:56:23,505 --> 00:56:26,966
for Nora to think of me
as a heartless father.

798
00:57:15,265 --> 00:57:16,808
They used to enjoy eating chocolate.

799
00:57:17,308 --> 00:57:18,434
Bom and Eun-joo, I mean.

800
00:57:20,103 --> 00:57:21,187
Yeah.

801
00:57:21,771 --> 00:57:24,774
I used to find it annoying when Ms. Song
called her Ms. Kang with respect,

802
00:57:24,858 --> 00:57:28,319
and the other assistants
called her a princess.

803
00:57:28,403 --> 00:57:30,238
But hearing about the arranged marriage,

804
00:57:30,321 --> 00:57:32,198
it really feels like
she lives in another world.

805
00:57:33,867 --> 00:57:36,453
But it's also a crucial part
of our next objective.

806
00:57:39,747 --> 00:57:42,000
If I'm being honest, I do feel bad

807
00:57:42,083 --> 00:57:44,711
about the hostility I showed her
after I learned who her father was.

808
00:57:45,712 --> 00:57:48,256
After all, she was also used
to make a borrowed-name account,

809
00:57:48,339 --> 00:57:49,757
just because she's his daughter.

810
00:57:50,258 --> 00:57:52,802
There's no reason for her
to participate in this theft,

811
00:57:53,303 --> 00:57:55,930
especially when her father is the target.

812
00:58:03,563 --> 00:58:04,397
Hello?

813
00:58:04,481 --> 00:58:06,483
Aunt Nora and President Shin's engagement
was called off.

814
00:58:07,567 --> 00:58:09,861
They called off the engagement? Why?

815
00:58:09,944 --> 00:58:10,778
It's canceled?

816
00:58:13,406 --> 00:58:15,074
Hey guys.

817
00:58:23,041 --> 00:58:24,167
What happened to you?

818
00:58:27,003 --> 00:58:29,714
I fell while climbing over the dorm walls.

819
00:58:30,215 --> 00:58:32,008
I had nowhere else to go.

820
00:58:34,052 --> 00:58:35,762
- Come in.
- Come on.

821
00:58:41,684 --> 00:58:43,186
We'll get you a change of clothes.

822
00:58:45,980 --> 00:58:47,190
Why did they call it off?

823
00:58:47,982 --> 00:58:48,942
I'm not sure.

824
00:58:52,195 --> 00:58:53,029
Oh my god.

825
00:59:12,507 --> 00:59:13,383
Here.

826
00:59:17,262 --> 00:59:18,930
What is all that money about?

827
00:59:21,224 --> 00:59:22,350
You must be thirsty. Here.

828
00:59:24,310 --> 00:59:25,228
Drink up.

829
00:59:28,648 --> 00:59:29,899
You remember

830
00:59:29,983 --> 00:59:32,610
I was awarded the Outstanding Woman
a few months ago, right?

831
00:59:33,611 --> 00:59:35,154
- Yes.
- Not too long after that,

832
00:59:35,238 --> 00:59:38,241
twenty-four billion won was deposited
into Hong Jang-mi's account.

833
00:59:39,284 --> 00:59:41,744
It was Hanmin's secret slush fund.

834
00:59:43,454 --> 00:59:45,290
So the day I filled in for Ms. Hong,

835
00:59:45,373 --> 00:59:47,625
you two were busy stealing
that huge amount of money.

836
00:59:47,709 --> 00:59:48,543
Right?

837
00:59:49,794 --> 00:59:52,755
Wait, how much is all that?

838
00:59:53,256 --> 00:59:54,299
It's too much.

839
00:59:55,174 --> 00:59:57,885
There's even more under your name.

840
00:59:57,969 --> 00:59:59,929
What? Me? Why?

841
01:00:00,013 --> 01:00:02,724
I know this is important and all,

842
01:00:02,807 --> 01:00:04,767
but what happened
with the engagement today?

843
01:00:07,061 --> 01:00:10,523
If I'm being honest,
I had a feeling this would happen.

844
01:00:11,649 --> 01:00:16,112
I overheard my father
talking to Ms. Song a few days ago.

845
01:00:16,571 --> 01:00:18,740
Then they should've postponed it
or canceled the party.

846
01:00:18,823 --> 01:00:19,741
Why did they proceed?

847
01:00:22,327 --> 01:00:24,329
That's just the kind of person
my father is.

848
01:00:25,830 --> 01:00:27,790
Even when I was kidnapped as a kid,

849
01:00:28,291 --> 01:00:30,460
he refused to pay the ransom

850
01:00:31,002 --> 01:00:32,503
and gave me up immediately.

851
01:00:37,258 --> 01:00:40,595
You two can never win against him alone.

852
01:00:41,346 --> 01:00:44,057
You need the money
hidden under my name too, right?

853
01:00:48,686 --> 01:00:49,520
That money…

854
01:00:50,647 --> 01:00:52,482
can be withdrawn by you.

855
01:00:52,982 --> 01:00:56,402
Just as I withdrew the money
under Hong Jang-mi's name.

856
01:01:05,078 --> 01:01:09,499
SEOUL CITY DORMITORY
FOR SINGLE FEMALE WORKERS

857
01:01:11,751 --> 01:01:12,585
Kang Nora!

858
01:01:12,669 --> 01:01:14,253
I knew you'd be here.

859
01:01:14,337 --> 01:01:16,381
Seriously, you couldn't go anywhere else?

860
01:01:16,881 --> 01:01:18,508
You'd better tell me the truth.

861
01:01:19,050 --> 01:01:20,385
President Shin dumped you, didn't he?

862
01:01:21,010 --> 01:01:22,595
I dumped him!

863
01:01:22,679 --> 01:01:24,097
As if!

864
01:01:24,722 --> 01:01:26,599
That's what he and I agreed upon!

865
01:01:26,683 --> 01:01:27,642
Who cares?

866
01:01:27,725 --> 01:01:29,477
We were completely humiliated
for all to see!

867
01:01:29,560 --> 01:01:30,603
Ma'am.

868
01:01:30,687 --> 01:01:33,815
Nora must be exhausted,
so you should be gentle with her.

869
01:01:35,358 --> 01:01:36,609
And who are you?

870
01:01:38,069 --> 01:01:39,278
She's my friend, Hong Jang-mi.

871
01:01:39,362 --> 01:01:40,446
I told you about her.

872
01:01:41,489 --> 01:01:42,323
Right.

873
01:01:43,408 --> 01:01:45,660
I'm just very much on edge right now.

874
01:01:46,202 --> 01:01:47,995
Let's go home. Your dad's waiting.

875
01:01:48,079 --> 01:01:49,956
You must be out of your damn mind. Get in!

876
01:01:54,293 --> 01:01:55,128
Let's go.

877
01:02:05,847 --> 01:02:08,725
She's so afraid of defying her father.

878
01:02:08,808 --> 01:02:10,184
You think she'll accept our offer?

879
01:02:11,936 --> 01:02:13,312
Maybe we shared too much?

880
01:02:30,496 --> 01:02:31,497
<i>That money</i>

881
01:02:31,581 --> 01:02:33,708
can be withdrawn by you.

882
01:02:34,208 --> 01:02:37,628
Just as I withdrew the money
under Hong Jang-mi's name.

883
01:02:38,212 --> 01:02:41,215
Where is that money right now?

884
01:02:43,050 --> 01:02:44,093
In Switzerland.

885
01:02:49,557 --> 01:02:50,558
And this is

886
01:02:51,184 --> 01:02:53,561
the evidence
the late President Kang Myeong-hwi

887
01:02:53,644 --> 01:02:55,730
was going to use
to blow the whistle on Hanmin.

888
01:02:56,355 --> 01:02:58,649
We believe his accident in July

889
01:02:58,733 --> 01:03:00,693
wasn't a coincidence.

890
01:03:04,363 --> 01:03:05,907
- Mom.
- What?

891
01:03:06,407 --> 01:03:07,784
I want to go on a trip.

892
01:03:09,202 --> 01:03:10,411
What?

893
01:03:10,495 --> 01:03:11,746
Where? The US?

894
01:03:11,829 --> 01:03:13,539
You want to go to the US?

895
01:03:13,623 --> 01:03:14,457
No.

896
01:03:15,500 --> 01:03:16,334
Switzerland.

897
01:03:17,585 --> 01:03:18,419
Switzerland?

898
01:03:27,512 --> 01:03:28,429
Will President Shin be fired?

899
01:03:29,013 --> 01:03:30,264
He should be.

900
01:03:30,348 --> 01:03:31,224
Of course.

901
01:03:32,350 --> 01:03:35,186
He must've expected as much
when he called off the marriage.

902
01:03:36,521 --> 01:03:37,605
In the Republic of Korea?

903
01:03:38,898 --> 01:03:42,777
There's no hard line between
the professional and personal here.

904
01:03:43,736 --> 01:03:47,031
I have been by the chairman's side
for 26 years now, so I know.

905
01:03:47,740 --> 01:03:50,409
He's going to tighten
things up internally now.

906
01:03:50,493 --> 01:03:51,410
That's when

907
01:03:52,286 --> 01:03:55,081
you push past Nora and rise to the top.

908
01:03:56,040 --> 01:03:57,375
This is a golden opportunity, okay?

909
01:03:58,292 --> 01:03:59,126
Okay.

910
01:04:00,127 --> 01:04:01,087
All right then.

911
01:04:32,201 --> 01:04:34,453
Where are all the files
that were on my desk?

912
01:04:34,537 --> 01:04:36,789
The Audit Division took everything.

913
01:04:37,290 --> 01:04:38,541
The chairman ordered them to.

914
01:04:41,043 --> 01:04:45,256
Ms. Song said you're free to leave
without saying your farewells.

915
01:04:54,432 --> 01:04:57,476
Thank you for your hard work.

916
01:04:58,394 --> 01:04:59,312
Not at all.

917
01:05:17,038 --> 01:05:19,248
Please take good care of Hong Keum-bo.

918
01:05:27,757 --> 01:05:30,343
- He hasn't even been here that long.
- I know, right?

919
01:06:11,968 --> 01:06:14,762
I see Ms. Go is incredibly diligent
about sharing my location.

920
01:06:14,845 --> 01:06:17,556
Thanks to her, you have
someone to see you off now.

921
01:06:18,349 --> 01:06:19,725
How does it feel to be fired?

922
01:06:20,518 --> 01:06:23,396
Being rejected by the organization
you once belonged to…

923
01:06:24,105 --> 01:06:24,939
It sucks, doesn't it?

924
01:06:25,022 --> 01:06:30,653
Both Hanmin and DK Ventures
have decided that I am of no use to them.

925
01:06:30,736 --> 01:06:32,196
It sucks a lot.

926
01:06:33,114 --> 01:06:35,199
Hong Keum-bo's asking makes it worse.

927
01:06:38,703 --> 01:06:41,038
Meet me at the street stall
in Yeouido tonight.

928
01:06:41,872 --> 01:06:42,748
Why?

929
01:06:42,832 --> 01:06:44,709
Aren't you done with me now that I'm out?

930
01:07:04,270 --> 01:07:05,938
ELIMINATING CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM'S
INNER CIRCLE

931
01:07:06,022 --> 01:07:07,189
STEP 1: PRESIDENT SHIN JUNG-WOO
ELIMINATED

932
01:07:15,197 --> 01:07:16,741
JANUARY 1998

933
01:07:16,824 --> 01:07:18,284
You've reached Song Ju-ran.

934
01:07:18,367 --> 01:07:19,201
<i>It's Hong Keum-bo.</i>

935
01:07:20,119 --> 01:07:21,203
You don't even hide it now?

936
01:07:22,246 --> 01:07:23,456
You need to keep your promise.

937
01:07:24,331 --> 01:07:25,833
<i>You broke that promise</i>

938
01:07:25,916 --> 01:07:27,376
<i>when you sent</i>
<i>that crazy burglar to my dorm.</i>

939
01:07:28,002 --> 01:07:29,962
<i>I sent you a gift,</i>

940
01:07:30,046 --> 01:07:31,255
<i>so enjoy.</i>

941
01:07:33,758 --> 01:07:34,633
Come in.

942
01:07:36,594 --> 01:07:38,012
This came for you, ma'am.

943
01:07:49,774 --> 01:07:51,734
REPORT ON THE STATUS
OF LARGE SHAREHOLDINGS

944
01:07:51,817 --> 01:07:54,153
SECTION 1: SUMMARY

945
01:07:54,653 --> 01:07:56,906
HELD BY: YEOUIDO PIRATES
CEO: HONG KEUM-BO

946
01:08:00,743 --> 01:08:03,370
MARKET PURCHASE OF SHARES (OVER 9%)

947
01:08:23,516 --> 01:08:25,226
Where is Hong Jang-mi?

948
01:08:25,935 --> 01:08:27,520
Maybe she's at the IT Division?

949
01:08:28,771 --> 01:08:29,605
What's this?

950
01:08:31,315 --> 01:08:32,900
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

951
01:08:32,983 --> 01:08:34,068
A resignation letter?

952
01:08:34,151 --> 01:08:35,736
Ms. Hong, this brat…

953
01:08:36,403 --> 01:08:37,488
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

954
01:08:37,571 --> 01:08:39,573
Is this company a joke to her?

955
01:09:06,350 --> 01:09:07,476
Hong Keum-bo.

956
01:09:09,353 --> 01:09:12,022
I confirmed that the FSS
processed her resignation.

957
01:09:14,400 --> 01:09:15,359
Hong Keum-bo,

958
01:09:16,443 --> 01:09:17,903
under the Yeouido Pirates' name,

959
01:09:18,779 --> 01:09:21,323
managed to buy up 9% of Hanmin's stocks.

960
01:09:23,951 --> 01:09:26,162
She dared to buy
our stocks with that money?

961
01:09:27,538 --> 01:09:28,539
Damn.

962
01:09:29,373 --> 01:09:30,457
I mean,

963
01:09:31,750 --> 01:09:34,170
she could've lived out her whole life
with that money.

964
01:09:34,253 --> 01:09:36,463
Why go through the trouble?
What's the point?

965
01:09:38,799 --> 01:09:40,092
What matters is

966
01:09:40,843 --> 01:09:43,179
that the chairman's slush fund is gone.

967
01:09:44,305 --> 01:09:46,307
Listen, we can just retrieve

968
01:09:46,891 --> 01:09:49,101
the money that was stolen, all right?

969
01:09:49,185 --> 01:09:51,103
If we crack down hard--

970
01:09:51,187 --> 01:09:52,021
No.

971
01:09:53,022 --> 01:09:54,440
Don't act rashly.

972
01:09:55,357 --> 01:09:56,775
The risk is too high.

973
01:09:58,027 --> 01:10:01,071
Tail Hong Keum-bo and keep me updated
on her whereabouts and who she meets.

974
01:10:02,865 --> 01:10:05,826
I need to figure out
how many insiders are involved first.

975
01:10:18,255 --> 01:10:19,256
Have a good night.

976
01:10:25,763 --> 01:10:27,389
Ma'am, a bottle of soju please.

977
01:10:27,473 --> 01:10:28,307
All right.

978
01:10:34,230 --> 01:10:35,064
Here you go.

979
01:10:38,525 --> 01:10:39,902
Look at you waiting patiently.

980
01:10:39,985 --> 01:10:43,113
Are you dressed like that because you're
no longer afraid of getting caught?

981
01:10:43,989 --> 01:10:46,283
I've never stopped being me.

982
01:10:46,367 --> 01:10:49,954
I used Song Ju-ran
to drive out President Shin Jung-woo.

983
01:10:50,037 --> 01:10:51,580
I thought as much.

984
01:10:52,081 --> 01:10:53,457
Congratulations on the achievement.

985
01:10:53,540 --> 01:10:56,335
And now I need an M&A expert
who can help me

986
01:10:56,418 --> 01:10:58,254
secure management control.

987
01:11:09,098 --> 01:11:11,684
REPORT ON THE STATUS
OF LARGE SHAREHOLDINGS

988
01:11:12,268 --> 01:11:13,644
Yeouido Pirates?

989
01:11:13,727 --> 01:11:15,896
I'm trying to recruit you right now,
Shin Jung-woo.

990
01:11:17,398 --> 01:11:19,275
Join Yeouido Pirates.

991
01:11:32,371 --> 01:11:36,250
SPECIAL THANKS TO SHIN YU-NA
FOR HER APPEARANCE

992
01:12:07,489 --> 01:12:09,325
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

993
01:12:09,992 --> 01:12:11,702
Yeouido Pirates is back.

994
01:12:12,369 --> 01:12:13,704
<i>I will appoint</i>

995
01:12:13,787 --> 01:12:16,498
<i>whoever catches the Captain first</i>

996
01:12:16,582 --> 01:12:18,292
<i>as the president.</i>

997
01:12:18,375 --> 01:12:19,752
<i>It must be a coincidence.</i>

998
01:12:19,835 --> 01:12:22,421
<i>Only the chairman and I know</i>
<i>about that Swiss account.</i>

999
01:12:22,504 --> 01:12:24,631
<i>Kang Nora is in Switzerland right now.</i>

1000
01:12:24,715 --> 01:12:27,134
<i>How are you so sure</i>
<i>that Kang Nora will take your side?</i>

1001
01:12:27,718 --> 01:12:28,886
Ms. Song's safe.

1002
01:12:28,969 --> 01:12:30,429
<i>That's the gold mine.</i>

1003
01:12:30,512 --> 01:12:33,515
<i>Is Hanmin surrounded by hostile forces,</i>

1004
01:12:33,599 --> 01:12:35,392
<i>just waiting to strike?</i>

1005
01:12:35,476 --> 01:12:37,186
<i>The Captain of Yeouido Pirates.</i>

1006
01:12:37,269 --> 01:12:38,228
<i>I know who it is.</i>

1007
01:12:40,689 --> 01:12:45,694
Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim
